(DYNAMIC PROFILING ANALYSIS WRITE-UP) Tj
T*
(===================================) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Objective) Tj
T*
(---------) Tj
T*
(The goal was to run dynamic profiling on the Address API and measure both CPU and memory) Tj
T*
(utilization.) Tj
T*
(We also needed to identify which functions/steps consumed the most resources and explain why.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What We Ran) Tj
T*
(----------) Tj
T*
(1\) Build:) Tj
T*
(   npm run build) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2\) Live profiling run \(server\):) Tj
T*
(   ENV=dev SERVER_PORT=5001 node --cpu-prof --cpu-prof-name=cpu.cpuprofile --heap-prof) Tj
T*
(--heap-prof-name=heap.heapprofile dist/src/server.js) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3\) Dynamic endpoint workload:) Tj
T*
(   Repeated POST requests to:) Tj
T*
(   - /address/distance) Tj
T*
(   - /address/request) Tj
T*
(   - /address/format) Tj
T*
(   - /address/count) Tj
T*
(   - /address/zipcode) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4\) Endpoint timing benchmark:) Tj
T*
(   Used curl time_total measurements across 10 runs per endpoint.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5\) Focused compute benchmark:) Tj
T*
(   Ran a high-iteration loop calling getDistance\(...\) to isolate pure math CPU cost.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(6\) Memory footprint check:) Tj
T*
(   Used /usr/bin/time -l to capture max resident set size and peak memory footprint.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Measured Results) Tj
T*
(----------------) Tj
T*
(Endpoint latency \(avg of 10 calls each\):) Tj
T*
(- distance: avg 1.75 ms, max 6.55 ms) Tj
T*
(- request:  avg 0.84 ms, max 1.04 ms) Tj
T*
(- format:   avg 0.78 ms, max 1.09 ms) Tj
T*
(- count:    avg 0.86 ms, max 0.97 ms) Tj
T*
(- zipcode:  avg 0.77 ms, max 0.86 ms) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(CPU hotspot findings:) Tj
T*
(- In the focused CPU profile, getDistance\(...\) was a major hotspot \(~35.42% sampled CPU share\).) Tj
