(- Garbage collector activity was present \(~9.26%\).) Tj
T*
(- Remaining samples included caller/loop overhead and runtime internals.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Memory utilization findings:) Tj
T*
(- Focused compute run max RSS: 45,842,432 bytes \(~43.7 MB\).) Tj
T*
(- Peak memory footprint reported: 13,849,472 bytes \(~13.2 MB\).) Tj
T*
(- During endpoint traffic sampling, memory remained stable \(no leak pattern observed\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why These Results Happened) Tj
T*
(-------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(The distance endpoint took the most time because it does more CPU work than the other routes:) Tj
T*
(- Input parsing and validation) Tj
T*
(- Degree-to-radian conversions) Tj
T*
(- Repeated trigonometric calculations \(sin, cos, atan2, sqrt\) in Haversine math) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(In contrast, other endpoints are mostly I/O-style request handling, formatting, or counting, so) Tj
T*
(they return faster.) Tj
T*
(Memory stayed relatively stable because request payloads are small and handlers complete) Tj
T*
(quickly without retaining long-lived objects.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What Is Within My Control \(Future Improvements\)) Tj
T*
(------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
(1\) Reduce redundant math in getDistance:) Tj
T*
(   Convert and reuse values once per request where possible.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2\) Add memoization for repeated coordinate pairs:) Tj
T*
(   If common points are requested frequently, caching can reduce repeated computation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3\) Keep profiling in production-like runs:) Tj
T*
(   Test-only profiles include TypeScript/Jest overhead, which can hide real endpoint hotspots.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4\) Track latency percentiles \(P50/P95\), not only average:) Tj
T*
(   This gives a better view of user experience under heavier load.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5\) Tune log volume in high-throughput paths:) Tj
T*
(   Logging overhead can become significant at scale.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Conclusion) Tj
T*
(----------) Tj
T*
(Dynamic profiling showed that the service is memory-stable and generally fast, with the primary) Tj
T*
(CPU-intensive path being distance calculation \(getDistance\).) Tj
T*
(This is expected based on the math-heavy nature of that endpoint.) Tj
T*
(The best next optimizations are math-path efficiency improvements and better runtime) Tj
T*
(observability.) Tj
T*
() Tj
